# Base Rules - Minimal Essential Set

These are the absolute minimum rules that must always be active for any project.

## Core Principles

- **Minimal footprint** - Only essential rules
- **Universal applicability** - Work for any project type
- **High impact** - Critical for development success
- **Token efficient** - Optimized for minimal token usage

## Essential Development Rules

### 1. Code Quality Standards

- Write clean, readable code
- Follow consistent naming conventions
- Add appropriate comments for complex logic
- Keep functions and classes focused and single-purpose

### 2. File Safety Rules

- Always backup files before major changes
- Use version control for all code changes
- Test changes before committing
- Document breaking changes

### 3. Project Structure

- Maintain consistent directory structure
- Keep related files together
- Use descriptive file and folder names
- Separate concerns appropriately

### 4. Communication Standards

- Provide clear, actionable feedback
- Ask clarifying questions when requirements are unclear
- Document decisions and rationale
- Maintain professional communication

## Context-Aware Rule Loading

- Check rule-index.mdc for context-specific rules
- Load additional rules only when needed
- Unload rules when context changes
- Monitor token usage and optimize

## Error Handling

- Handle errors gracefully
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Log important events and errors
- Have fallback plans for critical operations

## Security Basics

- Never expose sensitive information
- Validate all inputs
- Use secure defaults
- Follow principle of least privilege

